  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a heavy pot over medium heat.",
    "Add chicken thighs and brown on all sides until golden.",
    "Remove chicken and set aside.",
    "In the same pot, stir in butter until melted.",
    "Add onion and garlic, cook until translucent.",
    "Toss in diced yellow pepper and cook for 3 minutes.",
    "Pour in chicken broth and bring to a simmer.",
    "Return chicken thighs to pot, cover, and cook until chicken reaches 165°F, about 20 minutes.",
    "Remove chicken, shred with two forks, and return to pot.",
    "Stir in heavy cream, season with salt and pepper, and heat until slightly thickened.",
    "Serve hot over rice or with crusty bread."
